# APIs and integration — [[project_name]]

## lib/apis/ structure

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `apis/clients/` | Retrofit `@RestApi` interfaces |
| `apis/interceptors/` | Dio interceptors (auth, logging) |
| `apis/common/` | Shared API types |
| `apis/core/` | API module wiring |

## When to add API code

Add Retrofit services when an epic needs new HTTP endpoints. Domain DTOs live in `lib/domain/<entity>/infrastructure/<entity>_dto.dart`; the Retrofit client typically lives in `infrastructure/<entity>_service.dart`.

## Integration wiring (subagent: integration-wiring)

After domain and feature layers exist:

1. **router.dart** — import new page, add `GoRoute` with path and name consistent with existing routes.
2. **injection.dart** — ensure `configureDependencies()` covers new `@injectable` classes.
3. **error_localizer.dart** — add `localize<Entity>Failure` method per new `*_failure.dart`.
4. **build_runner** — run after Injectable/Freezed/Retrofit changes:
   ```
   dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
   ```

## Rules

- No UI in `lib/apis/`.
- Presentation never calls Retrofit directly — use repository from domain.
